headline: Synchrony Makes a Comeback in Credit Cards at Walmart
summary: The search for  Walmart’s  new credit-card issuer after a messy breakup with  Capital One Financial  is over.  The new suitor is a familiar face—  Synchrony  Financial, which has run the retailer’s credit-card program before.  OnePay, a fintech backed by Walmart, chose Synchrony to head up the credit-card program, the companies said Monday.
